# Clinical Service — AtlasOS Agent Rules

## PHI/PII Safety
- Never log PHI in plaintext. Redact at source.
- All database queries returning patient data must use parameterized queries.
- Test data must use synthetic patients, never real patient data.

## Code Standards
- All API endpoints must have input validation and output sanitization.
- All clinical data models must include audit fields (created_by, updated_by, timestamps).
- FHIR resources must validate against R4 schemas before persistence.

## Deployment Safety
- All changes require passing CI (unit + integration + compliance tests).
- Database migrations must be reversible (up + down).
- Feature flags required for patient-facing changes.

## Autonomous Operations
- Auto-fix linting errors and type issues.
- Auto-update dependencies with passing tests (patch versions only).
- Propose PRs for minor versions; require human review for major versions.
